        "id": "docling_magazine_TheEconomist.2024.02.24_page_008_23",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Rivian forecast that its output of electric trucks would be flat this year and that it would cut 10% of its staff. Rivian's 1Po in 2021 pushed its market value above that of General Motors, but its share price has fallen by almost 90% since then.",
        "bbox": [
